Operatives of The Delta State Police Command have arrested twenty-five suspected cultists in Agbor. The Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Bright Edafe who confirmed the report in a statement said, “some of the suspects confessed being members of Black Axe Confraternity and Junior Supreme Aiye Confraternity.’’ According to him, an investigation is ongoing, adding that the Delta State Commissioner of Police, CP Ari Muhammed Ali appreciated officers and men for their tireless efforts in the fight against crime and criminality in the State.